AMS round 1 (2026) delete parcel in response, change mind (test only)


Key details
Description

Test scenarios for deleting a parcel

and change your mind 

No changes from last years functionality (test only cases)

Scenario 1 - I delete a parcel as an AMS reponse

Scenario 2 - I undo the delete

Scenario 3 - I change my mind from accept to reject (pre submit)

Scenario 4 - I change claimed area, then uncheck EH box, claimed area change is reverted

Steps to Reproduce / Requirement Steps


Scenario 1: I wish to apply to delete a parcel on AMS
Given I am logged in as Advisor and or Farmer -
If an agent, I select AMS from Agent tools and select a client to go to Farmer Dashboard
If a farmer, I see AMS panel on Farmer Dashboard
And I press Respond to Findings
And I see a list of all parcels – Reds only Round 1
And there is a View map icon on the end of each parcel line
And the AMS findings column is populated with Artificial Surface
And I see my red parcels with a red symbol for response required
And I select a parcel
And side drawer opens
And I see option to delete the parcel (bin symbol)
And I press delete
And i will see a pop up message (in side drawer)
And i will be asked to confirm delete parcel that I am deleting (or cancel)
And I will see a message on the AMS modal "You have requested to delete this parcel from your BISS application. This may affect payment on other Area based schemes. Please undo if this was done in error"
And I save changes
And i see a strikethrough the parcel to indicate it is deleted
And status of parcel will be blank
And I will see a green toast message "You have successfully marked parcel X for deletion"
And i see a yellow warning now at top of AMS response screen "You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments"

Scenario 2: I wish to undo the delete of a parcel
Given I am logged in as Advisor and or Farmer -
If an agent, I select AMS from Agent tools and select a client to go to Farmer Dashboard
If a farmer, I see AMS panel on Farmer Dashboard
And I press Respond to Findings
And I see a list of all parcels – Reds only Round 1
And there is a View map icon on the end of each parcel line
And the AMS findings column is populated with Artificial Surface
And I see my red parcels with a red symbol for response required
And i select the parcel that has a strikethrough it
And i see option to recover on the parcel line
And i press recover
And the warning message will now be gone "You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments"
And parcel shows original values (no response selected)
And the edit panel side drawer is open
And I save changes
And no strike through the parcel line

Scenario 3: I have responded to some of my notifications and I crash (before submitting), and I change my mind from accept to reject
Given I am logged in as Advisor and or Farmer -
If an agent, I select AMS from Agent tools and select a client to go to Farmer Dashboard
If a farmer, I see AMS panel on Farmer Dashboard
And I press Respond to Findings
And I see a list of all parcels – Reds only Round 1
And I have accepted my AMS findings on a parcel X
And I have drawn the map
And pressed save (dont submit)
Now I wish to go back in and change my response for that parcel X
And I select the parcel X
And side drawer opens
And I press reject
And i select a reason from the list
And I press Save
And a call to LPIS occurs to delete any map drawn

Scenario 4 : I change my mind (have changed claimed area, then uncheck the EH box)
Given I am logged in as Advisor and or Farmer -
If an agent, I select AMS from Agent tools and select a client to go to Farmer Dashboard
If a farmer, I see AMS panel on Farmer Dashboard
And I press Respond to Findings
And I see a list of all parcels – Reds only Round 1
And I have accepted my AMS findings on a parcel X
And I have drawn the map
And I have check request change of EH
And I have changed the claimed area
And pressed save
Now I wish to go back in and change my response for that parcel X
And I select the same parcel
And I UNCHECK request change of EH
Claimed area should revert to original
